From a48f615a5e108a9c3e9b1bae82269090fdf868c3 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Thu, 4 Jun 2026 06:23:02 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Add landing/home split, Uncle Ross mascot, new pages and
 Guardian Mode

Reworks the site into a public landing + gated home/hub flow with
GitHub-style motion, gradients and Rhodes-purple branding.

Highlights
- New landing page (/) with aurora hero, parallax mascot, Sign up /
  Log in / Browse as guest, count-up stats and rich About/Founder/
  Suggest CTAs.
- New /home hub gated behind auth or guest mode; client-side gate
  bounces visitors back to landing with ?next=.
- New pages: /about (interactive pillars + FAQ), /founder (flip
  portrait, timeline, vision), /rides (trip planner + Guardian Mode
  prototype + verified-driver directory), /suggest (feedback board,
  backed by new /api/suggestions endpoint), /developers (stack, API
  reference, open roadmap).
- News rebuilt with curated bursaries, student opportunities and SA
  academic events, multi-page article modal and external apply links.
- Uncle Ross the Rhodent SVG mascot with wave/blink/tail-wag.
- Shared auth-aware nav + footer rendered from app.js, used across
  every gated page for consistent chrome.
- Tailwind theme extended (aurora gradients, glass surfaces, shimmer,
  glow CTAs, reveal-on-scroll, tilt cards) and CSS rebuilt.
- Sell page now requires a real account (no guests); other gated
  pages allow guest browsing with read-only behavior.
